- Don't you remember the poem?

14
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:27,280
Oh yes... l remember.

15
00:01:27,719 --> 00:01:30,320
''O' traveller on the
path through fire''

16
00:01:30,719 --> 00:01:37,160
''Should you ever find
a tree on your way''

17
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:45,280
''Seek not even the shade of a leaf
For the path leads through fire''

18
00:01:46,239 --> 00:01:50,600
''Tread tirelessly and without rest
upon the path of fire''

19
00:01:50,879 --> 00:01:52,280
''Make unto yourselfthat promise''
- Oh no!

20
00:01:52,879 --> 00:01:55,360
Promise that!
- All right... l promise.

21
00:01:55,719 --> 00:01:59,000
''For traveller, you tread upon
the path through fire''

22
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,720
l forgot the next lines, Daddy.

23
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:03,160
''Thus he wades ...

24
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:11,160
... through a sea of
tears, sweat and blood''

25
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:15,400
''For the traveller, treads upon
the path through fire''

26
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:17,520
What does that stanza mean,
Daddy?

27
00:02:18,039 --> 00:02:21,920
Man must pass the test of fire...

28
00:02:22,039 --> 00:02:25,280
... by blood, toil, sweat and
tears.

29
00:02:25,879 --> 00:02:28,680
And then, no obstacle can stand
in the way ofwhat he seeks.

30
00:02:29,199 --> 00:02:32,280
l won't forget this poem ever.
l promise.

31
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:35,600
That's good, Son.
- Hello there, schoolmaster!

32
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:40,960
Electricity is coming to our village.
The engineer is here already.

33
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,520
Shiksha! Hey Shiksha!

34
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:50,000
How many times have l told you, Vijay,
not to run about! Watch your step!

35
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:52,280
Hey Shiksha!
- What's up, Brother?

36
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:55,000
Why! You're still sitting
beside the lamp! Just forget it!

37
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,040
Vey soon, we'll have the sun
brought right into our house.

38
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:59,440
