towards your death.

234
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:39,400
That's because your bosses
don't like being refused.

235
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:45,280
You've started refusing them too.
- To come up in life, it is...

236
00:24:45,640 --> 00:24:48,880
... necessay to refuse some things.
- This measure of self promotion...

237
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:53,400
... could be quite dangerous, Vijay.
You are involved in all their rackets.

238
00:24:54,519 --> 00:24:56,560
But you've refused to get
involved with narcotics.

239
00:24:57,720 --> 00:25:00,400
That's because you hate
narcotics just as l do.

240
00:25:02,119 --> 00:25:06,400
And l want to help you.
- No, thank you.

241
00:25:08,119 --> 00:25:11,560
l don't need your help.
Understand!

242
00:25:12,160 --> 00:25:15,400
And what exactly are you
tying to tell me?

243
00:25:16,519 --> 00:25:18,800
Are you telling me that they are
planning to kill me today?

244
00:25:21,119 --> 00:25:23,400
But, l know the exact time when
they want to kill me.

245
00:25:25,839 --> 00:25:28,960
Let me show you...
Take a look at this.

246
00:25:32,319 --> 00:25:37,120
Do you see what's written in there?
''6 o'clock- an appointment with Death''

247
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:39,040
This evening at six, l have an
appointment with death.

248
00:25:40,119 --> 00:25:42,720
An appointment... hear that? l
can also speak English, you know.

249
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:45,400
And now, l must take your leave.

250
00:25:47,519 --> 00:25:52,560
3 more hours to go, Usman.
Think it over again, ifyou may.

251
00:25:53,359 --> 00:25:56,400
All Vijay Chauhan wants, is the top
chair. Let's just give it to him.

252
00:25:56,920 --> 00:26:00,040
Don't bring trouble in here.
- Bloody coward!

253
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:02,040
lfyou are so scared, why did you
get into this business?

254
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:05,200
With Vijay at the helm, we'll have
to wash our hands off narcotics.

255
00:26:05,559 --> 00:26:07,400
And, that'd put paid our ambitions
to overtake Kancha Cheena.

256
00:26:08,920 --> 00:26:12,960
Why cy over spilt milk?
l'd warned you.

257
00:26:13,079 --> 00:26:17,800
And you had insisted saying that
he'd be a faithful dog forever.

258
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:23,280
Now your bloody dog refuses!

259
00:26:27,839 --> 00:26:30,200
We're going to
kill him at 6 O'clock today.

260
00:26:41,319 --> 00:26:44,120
Hi there, Vijay...come in...
Welcome.

261
00:26:45,519 --> 00:26:48,440
Come inside, dear.
Why are you standing outside?

262
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:53,400
Now you want a chair, don't you?
Here... have this chair.

263
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:56,600
Oh yes... the chair is for you.
We're old men now.

264
00:26:57,160 --> 00:27:00,720
We're simply waiting to die.
Come on.... take over.

265
00:27:13,519 --> 00:27:15,400
The phones keep ringing...

266
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:20,400
...over here... Don't they?

267
00:27:25,720 --> 00:27:27,600
The telephone is quite
a misleading instrument.

268
00:27:28,759 --> 00:27:33,200
People like you use the telephone
to say things you don't intend to.

269
00:27:33,319 --> 00:27:37,120
And you end up doing things quite
different from what you say.

270
00:27:37,519 --> 00:27:40,800
You're misinformed.
- No.

271
00:27:42,519 --> 00:27:44,400
Come over here.
- Who ...l?!

272
00:27:49,119 --> 00:27:50,800
lt's you who is tying to
mislead me.

273
00:27:52,400 --> 00:27:56,880
You're plotting to kill me. And when
confronted, you offer me the chair.

274
00:27:59,519 --> 00:28:05,120
Kill me ifyou want to. l'll
willingly face your bullets.

275
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:11,000
lfyou kill me, the business is
yours and the chair is yours too.

276
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:15,200
And what if l survive?

277
00:28:32,119 --> 00:28:38,280
The guns won't decide who wins
the war bemeen us... fate will.

278
00:29:51,279 --> 00:29:52,600
Why are you shooting at the
car?

279
00:29:54,519 --> 00:29:58,800
Shoot at me. Go on, shoot!

280
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:05,480
Go on... Iet's see some more
shooting.

281
00:30:08,519 --> 00:30:15,880
Swine! You've stabbed me in the back.
Shoot me when l'm facing you. Go on!

282
00:30:38,519 --> 00:30:42,400
Swine! Cur! Dog! Look at what
they've done to my stuff!

283
00:30:44,119 --> 00:30:48,400
Smashed my coconuts! Curse you!

284
00:31:06,880 --> 00:31:09,440
Don't breathe your last yet!
l'll save you! l will!

285
00:31:13,240 --> 00:31:15,120
Now give me your hand... your
hand!

286
00:31:15,519 --> 00:31:19,400
Wory not. l'll save you!

287
00:31:20,519 --> 00:31:23,960
l'll take you to a doctor.
Now keep breathing...

288
00:31:26,720 --> 00:31:27,880
Just keep on breathing.

289
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:33,840
Down the shutters!

290
00:31:34,079 --> 00:31:35,960
They dare to shoot at the Don!

291
00:31:41,079 --> 00:31:44,760
The Don needs blood!
Come along, folks.

292
00:31:48,119 --> 00:31:52,680
There was a bandit. Eveyone
in the city was fed up of him.

293
00:31:53,559 --> 00:31:57,360
He used to plunder for the sake of
money. Sometimes, he killed people.

294
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:02,280
Your son has been shot by his
rivals.

295
00:32:05,559 --> 00:32:06,840
He's in a hospital right now.

296
00:32:09,359 --> 00:32:12,640
We've imposed a curFew
to stop the riots in the city.

297
00:32:13,880 --> 00:32:16,280
You can come to hospital in my
jeep.

298
00:32:17,079 --> 00:32:20,280
Thank you for giving me
the news, Mr.Gaitonde.

299
00:32:22,799 --> 00:32:25,280
As all evil things meet an evil
end,...

300
00:32:26,920 --> 00:32:28,800
...so was it with the evil bandit.

301
00:32:31,559 --> 00:32:33,920
One day, he was shot dead.

302
00:33:04,160 --> 00:33:06,240
We have enough stock of blood in
the hospital. And you may leave now.

303
00:33:06,480 --> 00:33:11,840
What are you raving at? Do you
take me for a blood donor?

304
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:15,440
What else is it?- l took the
trouble to bring him here.

305
00:33:15,880 --> 00:33:17,760
Do you know how many coconuts
l have lost in the bargain?

306
00:33:18,559 --> 00:33:21,200
l've lost 325 rupees in all.
Are you going to compensate me?

307
00:33:38,079 --> 00:33:40,960
Come in, quickly.

308
00:33:46,960 --> 00:33:52,000
These fellows are savages!
They're screaming and throwing stones.

309
00:33:52,799 --> 00:33:55,520
l've taken a few stones too.
Bloody savages!

310
00:33:56,880 --> 00:34:00,880
l'm Krishnan lyer MA (postgraduate
in arts). And now, l sell coconuts.

311
00:34:01,680 --> 00:34:06,920
They nearly upturned my cart!
That's when l saw the Don.

312
00:34:07,359 --> 00:34:11,800
There was lots of blood.
Blood was pouring out of his body.

313
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:16,200
l brought him to the hospital. l did!
And now, they throw stones at me!

314
00:34:16,760 --> 00:34:20,040
l lost a lot of money in the bargain.
l had to throw a lot of coconuts away.

315
00:34:20,679 --> 00:34:22,560
The total loss is
something like 325 Rupees.

316
00:34:24,920 --> 00:34:26,720
These fellows are savages...
but... what brings you here?

317
00:34:28,360 --> 00:34:31,280
Well,... why have you come here?
- l'm his mother.

318
00:34:32,079 --> 00:34:33,560
His mother?!

319
00:34:39,559 --> 00:34:44,720
What up? No night cricket nowadays...
has a politician won an election?

320
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:48,720
And where are our guards?

321
00:34:51,639 --> 00:34:57,280
None ofthem seem to be around.
- Could it be that Vijay has survived?

322
00:35:02,039 --> 00:35:05,840
l'd warned you not to touch him.

323
00:35:06,559 --> 00:35:09,120
lf he survives,
all four of us are dead.

324
00:35:16,039 --> 00:35:19,520
No! That can't be!

325
00:35:21,039 --> 00:35:24,000
Let's kill him before he can kill
US.

326
00:35:24,239 --> 00:35:28,440
A thousand men are keeping vigil on
the hospital. How will you kill him?

327
00:35:30,239 --> 00:35:34,080
lnspector Pathan
will make it possible.

328
00:35:34,320 --> 00:35:36,320
For my sake, he will.

329
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:44,960
The Don is out of danger!
Hurrah! Let us celebrate...

330
00:36:05,599 --> 00:36:06,840
Excuse me... l'm Inspector Pathan.

331
00:36:06,960 --> 00:36:10,880
l am assigned to protectyour
SOn.

332
00:36:12,639 --> 00:36:16,720
Will you please ask the people
outside to disperse?

333
00:36:18,719 --> 00:36:22,000
Vijay is safe now.

334
00:36:27,239 --> 00:36:31,600
So the savages have now been
sent away! They even made me dance!

335
00:36:32,239 --> 00:36:34,120
They gave me this. l don't know
whether it's real gold or artificial!

336
00:36:35,239 --> 00:36:37,440
l'll be on my way now.
- Son...

337
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:44,120
l haven't enough
words to thank you...

338
00:36:46,239 --> 00:36:53,120
... for whatever you've
done for Vijay.

339
00:36:57,360 --> 00:36:58,720
You'll come back... won't you,
Son?

340
00:37:01,239 --> 00:37:05,840
l'd stayed back for my 325
rupees.

341
00:37:06,440 --> 00:37:10,440
l thought l'd leave aRer
l receive 325 rupees.

342
00:37:11,320 --> 00:37:14,840
And you've given me so much
more.- What do you mean?

343
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:19,920
l've been living for
many years on the sidewalk.

344
00:37:20,719 --> 00:37:22,120
l haven't ever been
addressed respectably.

345
00:37:23,360 --> 00:37:27,000
l'm used to hearing abusive
Ianguage.

346
00:37:28,280 --> 00:37:32,840
But you've addressed me as a son.
l will come. l surely will.

347
00:37:33,239 --> 00:37:36,680
l'll come, even if it is the
Iast thing l do before l die.

348
00:37:38,239 --> 00:37:41,440
l will come. l surely will.

349
00:37:52,119 --> 00:37:53,920
A black cat across my path!

350
00:37:56,039 --> 00:37:58,120
Now l have to take 10 steps
backwards (to ward offthe evil).

351
00:38:10,960 --> 00:38:14,720
Get out of here, you fool!
Else l'll cut your head for you.

352
00:38:15,239 --> 00:38:17,160
What did you say?
Will you cut my head off?

353
00:38:17,239 --> 00:38:19,680
Oh yes.- D'you know what l
could do to you?

354
00:38:20,559 --> 00:38:22,840
Just get out of here.-l'll thrash
the daylights out ofyou!

355
00:38:23,119 --> 00:38:24,840
Hey...!
- Bloody fellows...!

356
00:38:27,239 --> 00:38:30,600
Will you cut my head off?!

357
00:38:31,239 --> 00:38:33,120
Now, wait and see what
l am going to do to you.

358
00:38:34,239 --> 00:38:36,120
Hury! The patient could be dying!

359
00:38:37,039 --> 00:38:38,120
He wants my head!

360
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:44,800
Hury!

361
00:39:21,320 --> 00:39:23,840
They made fun of me out there.

362
00:39:24,239 --> 00:39:28,120
And, l told them, l'd show them
up.

363
00:39:31,440 --> 00:39:34,960
The Don isn't here at all.
He's inside the bathroom.

364
00:39:36,559 --> 00:39:41,120
Vijay Chavan survived the second
attempt. And l'm in a fix right now.

365
00:39:43,440 --> 00:39:47,120
Tell him, my life is in danger.

366
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:50,120
Vijay Chauhan is leaving
the hospital tomorrow.

367
00:39:50,559 --> 00:39:54,120
l'm taking the first flight to
Mauritius tomorrow. Tell him that.

368
00:40:11,199 --> 00:40:13,480
Vijay Chavan has survived
the second attempt.

369
00:40:20,760 --> 00:40:26,120
ARer a long while, an Indian fish
has appeared in my waters.

370
00:40:26,440 --> 00:40:30,800
lnvite him to dinner.
- But, Vijay Chavan...

371
00:40:31,159 --> 00:40:35,920
l'd like to befriend an enemy...

372
00:40:36,320 --> 00:40:38,120
... who gains a fresh lease of
life.

373
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:43,320
l could gain a fresh lease of life.
Have flowers sent to Vijay Chavan.

374
00:40:48,639 --> 00:40:54,720
Don! Please forgive me!
l've committed a grave error!

375
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:04,320
Kancha Cheena has
sent me these flowers.

376
00:41:06,239 --> 00:41:07,320
Nice flowers.

377
00:41:08,440 --> 00:41:11,320
Forgive me, Don! Please forgive
Me.

378
00:41:12,440 --> 00:41:14,320
Why is he weeping?

379
00:41:19,239 --> 00:41:20,800
His uniform is a symbol of his
power.

380
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:27,320
He can stop anyone he wants to.
He can let anyone in.

381
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:30,920
He can allow anyone to shoot.
- l won't make such a mistake again!

382
00:41:31,840 --> 00:41:33,320
Tell him not to do
such a thing again.

383
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:39,520
Does he want to die?
He doesn't want to, does he?

384
00:41:40,159 --> 00:41:42,800
Ask him to see reason. And he
must do my bidding from now on.

385
00:41:45,239 --> 00:41:47,320
Now get going... take him away.

386
00:41:50,719 --> 00:41:55,040
All right... go on now.
- Thank you, Don.

387
00:42:00,440 --> 00:42:03,920
Congratulations on
the fresh lease of your life.

388
00:42:04,840 --> 00:42:07,120
Now, you're the uncrowned king
ofthis city.

389
00:42:08,679 --> 00:42:13,040
Eveyone in the city is celebrating
your recovey... except your 4 bosses.

390
00:42:15,760 --> 00:42:21,480
l think you'd like to make your moves
aRer the enemy has exhausted theirs.

391
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:24,920
But l won't let you succeed in
any move.

392
00:42:25,440 --> 00:42:28,360
l'll stop you in evey path you
go like a wall.

393
00:42:29,760 --> 00:42:33,360
Because, l'm an honest police
officer who can't be bought &...

394
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:37,360
... who still lives off a meagre
salay of Rs.1500.

395
00:42:38,159 --> 00:42:39,320
Demand for a hike!

396
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:44,200
You should really hike
the salaries ofyour policemen.

397
00:42:46,440 --> 00:42:49,040
The salay isn't enough for a living.
Can it pay for the conscience?

398
00:42:55,440 --> 00:42:59,320
What's happening here? Now, go
on eveybody... please leave.

399
00:43:12,880 --> 00:43:13,840
Mummy...

400
00:43:15,840 --> 00:43:20,360
Your mother still ekes a livelihood
out of 500 Rupees a month.

401
00:43:30,039 --> 00:43:32,160
You've been lying unconscious
for the last 3 days.

402
00:43:32,280 --> 00:43:35,520
And your mother didn't move
for a moment all this while.

403
00:43:36,440 --> 00:43:38,280
She sat all the while,
and kept staring at you.

404
00:43:38,440 --> 00:43:40,200
And you...
- What's your name?

405
00:43:40,840 --> 00:43:43,200
Why do you want to know
that?

406
00:43:44,760 --> 00:43:48,800
You're the first woman aRer my
mother who has seen me naked.

407
00:43:50,440 --> 00:43:54,120
l was a child when l played on
her lap. And here l have been lying...

408
00:43:54,239 --> 00:43:56,840
...unconscious for 3 days. And you've
taken care of me. That's why l ask.

409
00:43:57,079 --> 00:43:59,000
What's your name?
- May Matthews.

410
00:44:00,360 --> 00:44:04,840
And l am Krishnan lyer, M.A.
Nowadays, l sell coconuts.

411
00:44:05,679 --> 00:44:09,560
l've been coming here for the last 3
days. Your men asked me not to leave.

412
00:44:09,880 --> 00:44:14,080
Oh, l know that they call you
a ''Don''. They told me that...

413
00:44:14,199 --> 00:44:16,840
...the Don would give me a reward.
l told them l don't want a reward.

414
00:44:17,159 --> 00:44:20,800
And l'll leave as soon as you
reimburse my loss of 325 Rupees.

415
00:44:22,039 --> 00:44:23,720
And will you keep
on standing over here?

416
00:44:26,760 --> 00:44:28,960
What if l don't give you the
325?

417
00:44:29,280 --> 00:44:35,840
No! You can't do something like that.
l picked you up and brought you here.

418
00:44:36,159 --> 00:44:38,240
Had l been 5 minutes late,
you could've died?

419
00:44:38,559 --> 00:44:40,520
Then l would've had to
take you to the crematorium.

420
00:44:41,960 --> 00:44:45,440
All right.
l'll let you have your 325.

421
00:44:46,760 --> 00:44:49,000
Now, Krishanan...
Oh yes, the MA.

422
00:44:51,800 --> 00:44:54,720
But you must promise me something.
- What?

423
00:44:55,960 --> 00:44:59,160
That you'll be there beside me should
anything like this happen again.

424
00:44:59,960 --> 00:45:03,320
Nothing's going to happen by God's.
grace. If something does,...

425
00:45:03,440 --> 00:45:06,240
...go wrong, l'll be
there a full five minutes earlier.

426
00:45:06,960 --> 00:45:10,160
And when l get angered,
l might do just about anything!

427
00:45:15,960 --> 00:45:19,160
Those are the bullets which were
taken out ofyou. They're useless now.

428
00:45:20,599 --> 00:45:24,800
Wait! Give me those leads.

429
00:45:36,039 --> 00:45:36,400
He'll be discharged from the hospital
tomorrow. And then, he'll kill us.

430
00:45:39,840 --> 00:45:42,440
Nothing ofthe sort will happen.
- Get out of my way!

431
00:45:42,960 --> 00:45:44,320
Hey! Shem ran out on us!

432
00:45:45,960 --> 00:45:48,440
Oh, hello! Where are you going?
- To hell!

433
00:45:48,960 --> 00:45:50,840
Get out of here.
Or will you save us still?

434
00:45:53,599 --> 00:45:55,440
Hello, Mr. Teylene!
How do you do?

435
00:45:59,960 --> 00:46:02,160
Greetings.
- Greetings.

436
00:46:02,960 --> 00:46:05,440
How are you, Don Usman?
Evemhing all right?

437
00:46:05,960 --> 00:46:13,800
Considering the present
circumstances, l conclude that...

438
00:46:14,840 --> 00:46:17,640
... there's one safe place...

439
00:46:18,159 --> 00:46:20,160
...where you will be in no danger.

440
00:46:20,679 --> 00:46:23,040
Where is it, Mr.Pathan?
- Where?!

441
00:46:23,679 --> 00:46:25,560
The lock up in my police station.

442
00:47:54,440 --> 00:47:56,440
Hello, Don Hasmukh.

443
00:47:59,679 --> 00:48:01,320
How are you, Don Usman?

444
00:48:03,840 --> 00:48:07,440
l have been faithful
to my masters for long.

445
00:48:10,559 --> 00:48:12,640
l always return whatever l take
from my masters with interest.

446
00:48:29,960 --> 00:48:33,320
No! Don't! Please, Don! Please
don't kill me!

447
00:48:36,960 --> 00:48:41,840
Please forgive me! l'll go back
to my village! l swear!

448
00:48:42,960 --> 00:48:44,920
Please don't kill me!

449
00:49:05,760 --> 00:49:08,320
Take your hand away.
Please take your hand away.

450
00:49:10,960 --> 00:49:12,440
Step aside.

451
00:49:29,800 --> 00:49:31,800
Why? What's up?

452
00:49:32,960 --> 00:49:36,040
Both ofyou seem troubled.

453
00:49:37,400 --> 00:49:40,320
The nurse was worried that
you...

454
00:49:40,960 --> 00:49:44,840
That l have run away!
No, doctor, l don't run away.

455
00:49:45,360 --> 00:49:49,520
Do l look like l'm about to
run away? l don't, do l?

456
00:49:50,840 --> 00:49:54,080
But ifyou don't discharge me
tomorrow,...

457
00:49:54,960 --> 00:49:57,720
...l'll surely kill a few people.

458
00:50:08,440 --> 00:50:11,240
Your bodyguards
weren't letting me in.

459
00:50:13,159 --> 00:50:14,840
Just as you don't
Iet me go out of here.

460
00:50:43,519 --> 00:50:47,840
Long live, Don Vijay.

